@SiobhanIde @zebullshit @Fair_Maiden1 @vicky_moriarty @iamjustanumber @Panderoona All parts of the brain stem testing protocol have to be performed twice by two consultants around a few hours apart. The time of brain stem death is recorded after the first set. They wait due to the high levels of co2 building up when the vent is paused to test for breathing.

@Fair_Maiden1 @JulietBrave @vicky_moriarty @iamjustanumber @Panderoona Every organ is being supported by a drug or a machine, the angiogram showed no blood flow to areas of the brain meaning the brain cells are dead. The poor lad has already coned which is irreversible. As sad as it is science is science. Let the lad go peacefully 🤦🏻‍♀️
@paulaweavis @thederrywan His bed is already costing over £5000 a day.

@thederrywan He would not make the transfer to a hospice and the minute they removed him from the ventilator he would “pass”. Palliative oxygen is not an option as he is not breathing for himself. The levels of support his organs are on makes him incredibly unstable to move.
